{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/stripe\/stpredirectcontext\/startredirectflow(from:)"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Starts a redirect flow.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You must ensure that your app delegate listens for  the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"returnURL"},{"type":"text","text":" that you"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"set on the Stripe object, and forwards it to the Stripe SDK so that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"context can be notified when the redirect is completed and dismiss the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"view controller. See "},{"code":"StripeAPI.handleURLCallback(with url:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The context will listen for both received URLs and app open notifications"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and fire its completion block when either the URL is received, or the next","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time the app is foregrounded."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The context will initiate the flow by presenting a SFSafariViewController","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instance from the passsed in view controller. If you want more manual control"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"over the redirect method, you can use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"startSafariViewControllerRedirectFlowFromViewController"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or ","type":"text"},{"code":"startSafariAppRedirectFlow","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the redirect supports a native app, and that app is is installed on the user’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"device, this call will do a direct app-to-app redirect instead of showing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a web url.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-ios\/documentation\/Stripe","doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-ios\/documentation\/Stripe\/STPRedirectContext"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"(startRedirectFlowFromViewController:) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"startRedirectFlow","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"from","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"presentingViewController","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UIViewController","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)UIViewController"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method does nothing if the context is not in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"STPRedirectContextStateNotStarted"},{"text":" state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parameter presentingViewController: The view controller to present the Safari"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view controller from."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-ios\/documentation\/Stripe\/STPRedirectContext\/startRedirectFlow(from:)"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","externalID":"c:@M@StripePayments@objc(cs)STPRedirectContext(im)startRedirectFlowFromViewController:","modules":[{"name":"Stripe"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"startRedirectFlow","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"from","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)UIViewController","text":"UIViewController","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method","title":"startRedirectFlow(from:)"},"references":{"doc://com.stripe.stripe-ios/documentation/Stripe/STPRedirectContext":{"url":"\/documentation\/stripe\/stpredirectcontext","title":"STPRedirectContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-ios\/documentation\/Stripe\/STPRedirectContext","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"STPRedirectContext","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"STPRedirectContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a helper class for handling redirects associated with STPSource and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"STPPaymentIntents.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Init and retain an instance with the Source or PaymentIntent you want to handle,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then choose a redirect method. The context will fire the completion handler","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when the redirect completes."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Due to the nature of iOS, very little concrete information can be gained","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"during this process, as all actions take place in either the Safari app","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or the sandboxed SFSafariViewController class. The context attempts to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"detect when the user has completed the necessary redirect action by listening"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for both app foregrounds and url callbacks received in the app delegate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, it is possible the when the redirect is “completed”, the user may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have not actually completed the necessary actions to authorize the charge.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"You should not use either this class, nor ","type":"text"},{"code":"STPAPIClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", as a way","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to determine when you should charge the Source or to determine if the redirect","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"was successful. Use Stripe webhooks on your backend server to listen for Source","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"state changes and to make the charge."}]},"doc://com.stripe.stripe-ios/documentation/Stripe/STPRedirectContext/startRedirectFlow(from:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"startRedirectFlow"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"from","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)UIViewController","text":"UIViewController","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-ios\/documentation\/Stripe\/STPRedirectContext\/startRedirectFlow(from:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/stripe\/stpredirectcontext\/startredirectflow(from:)","title":"startRedirectFlow(from:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Starts a redirect flow."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You must ensure that your app delegate listens for  the "},{"code":"returnURL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set on the Stripe object, and forwards it to the Stripe SDK so that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"context can be notified when the redirect is completed and dismiss the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view controller. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StripeAPI.handleURLCallback(with url:)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The context will listen for both received URLs and app open notifications"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and fire its completion block when either the URL is received, or the next","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time the app is foregrounded."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The context will initiate the flow by presenting a SFSafariViewController","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instance from the passsed in view controller. If you want more manual control","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"over the redirect method, you can use ","type":"text"},{"code":"startSafariViewControllerRedirectFlowFromViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"startSafariAppRedirectFlow"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the redirect supports a native app, and that app is is installed on the user’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"device, this call will do a direct app-to-app redirect instead of showing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a web url.","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.stripe.stripe-ios/documentation/Stripe":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/stripe","title":"Stripe","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-ios\/documentation\/Stripe","abstract":[]}}}